negative.review:
I really wish there was a "middle/neutral" rating for a game, but there isn't; 

While I think the idea and the charm of this game is really nice, the simple fact you have to constantly fight the game on if you can even get past the first or second round because the game just decides it doesn't want you to is frankly ridiculous. Once you play long enough you get so many items that dilute the pool you can almost never find what you want even while rerolling. These two things combined make it to where going for high reward builds for symbol valued higher than Cherries or Lemons is almost impossible, because if you don't take a luck item to start your run you can just lose the first 3 rounds with no chance to get going; this is especially annoying when you get an item and phone call combination for a specific high-rate symbol, then proceed to roll nothing or only cherries and lemons ending your run instantly. This is worsened by the 666 appearing on the third deadline itself (why not putting it on the 6th deadline and make that one 666?), meaning that by turn 3 and 4 when the game ACTUALLY begins you can get a 666, lose everything and get caught back in the original loop.

Do I understand it's a slot machine and it is literally random chance? Yes, I get that that's the novelty and interest, but it's also a video game that should allow players to both actually play and feel like they're progressing/understanding items and builds after playing for X amount of time, but it just doesn't.
